WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-US

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:04.569
Detective Recapped here. Today, I'm going
to explain a Mystery-Romance film called:

00:00:04.569 --> 00:00:08.780
"Killing Me Softly." Spoilers ahead! Watch
out and take care.

00:00:08.780 --> 00:00:12.309
As a group of mountaineers climbs a snowy
cliff, a woman describes how the brain dies

00:00:12.309 --> 00:00:16.670
from a lack of oxygen once a person reaches
a certain altitude. The brain just shuts down,

00:00:16.670 --> 00:00:20.019
and the body goes along with it. The woman
says she can't stop thinking about what it

00:00:20.019 --> 00:00:23.450
must have been like, and the person she's
talking to asks her to start from the beginning,

00:00:23.450 --> 00:00:25.470
so she tells him her whole story.

00:00:25.470 --> 00:00:29.609
An American woman named Alice describes her
life in London with her boyfriend, Jake. Alice

00:00:29.609 --> 00:00:33.350
says she grew up on the plains in Indiana
and that she's always been a flatlander. She

00:00:33.350 --> 00:00:36.440
had already been staying in London for a year
and a half, and the first six months have

00:00:36.440 --> 00:00:41.220
been hard on her, but that changed upon meeting
Jake. Alice is a CD-Roms and Website designer,

00:00:41.220 --> 00:00:43.060
while Jake is an engineer.

00:00:43.060 --> 00:00:46.921
One day, Alice is about to cross the street
when she encounters a charming stranger. She

00:00:46.921 --> 00:00:50.560
is completely enthralled by him as they cross,
and his very presence distracts her even after

00:00:50.560 --> 00:00:54.559
they parted ways. Alice starts heading inside
her office, but she takes another look at

00:00:54.559 --> 00:00:56.930
him and sees him entering a bookstore.

00:00:56.930 --> 00:01:01.300
After being continually distracted and unsettled
at work, she finally heads out. Peeking inside

00:01:01.300 --> 00:01:05.570
the bookstore, she sees that the man is waiting
in line with his friend. He looks at her,

00:01:05.570 --> 00:01:09.680
embarrassing her, so she steps back and hides.
When she's finally about to go inside, Alice

00:01:09.680 --> 00:01:13.630
finds herself face to face with the man, with
only the glass separating them.

00:01:13.630 --> 00:01:17.730
She accepted the stranger's offer to get inside
a cab with him. Inside the car, the sensual

00:01:17.730 --> 00:01:21.580
tension between them hangs heavy in the air.
After the man takes Alice home, he grabs her

00:01:21.580 --> 00:01:25.560
from behind and starts kissing her. Alice
then kisses him back, and it isn't long before

00:01:25.560 --> 00:01:30.030
they make torrid and passionate love. Once
they're done, Alice dresses and turns away,

00:01:30.030 --> 00:01:33.831
embarrassed and perhaps even regretful. After
softly asking her to face him, the stranger

00:01:33.831 --> 00:01:37.810
helps her put on her undergarment. Maintaining
a gentle tone, he invites her to come back

00:01:37.810 --> 00:01:41.950
to his house again, but Alice keeps insisting
that she can't. In the end, he assures her

00:01:41.950 --> 00:01:45.240
that she can come over whenever she wants
and that he'll be there when she does. That

00:01:45.240 --> 00:01:48.770
night, Alice makes love with Jake, but it
feels different and not nearly as thrilling

00:01:48.770 --> 00:01:50.680
as it did when she slept with the stranger.

00:01:50.680 --> 00:01:54.970
The following day, Alice passes by the bookstore
with the hopes of seeing the stranger again.

00:01:54.970 --> 00:01:59.210
Instead, she sees a poster of him along with
his book. There, she learns that the man is

00:01:59.210 --> 00:02:03.440
Adam Tallis, a mountain climber who saved
six people with no oxygen. After buying Adam's

00:02:03.440 --> 00:02:06.500
book, Alice goes straight to Adam's house,
where she finds him waiting for her by the

00:02:06.500 --> 00:02:10.000
door. The two make love once more, and afterwards,
they lie on the floor.

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:14.250
Now resting, Alice tells Adam that she bought
his book. He corrects her, saying that it's

00:02:14.250 --> 00:02:18.470
not his book; he's just in it. When she comments
that it looks good, he simply retorts that

00:02:18.470 --> 00:02:23.310
people died. Adam gets up to smoke, then starts
telling Alice what happened. According to

00:02:23.310 --> 00:02:26.980
Adam, he lost the whole group of mountaineers
he was with, including the woman he loved,

00:02:26.980 --> 00:02:31.030
Francoise Collette. There was no room for
error, everything had been checked, yet he

00:02:31.030 --> 00:02:34.330
still doesn't know what happened. He then
asks Alice if he knows what it's like over

00:02:34.330 --> 00:02:38.230
20,000 feet, and when Alice shakes her head,
Adam stands and snatches his goldfish from

00:02:38.230 --> 00:02:42.450
the aquarium. Adam shows Alice the fish as
it struggles to breathe, saying that's exactly

00:02:42.450 --> 00:02:47.400
how it feels. Without air, the brain cells
die. Once the brain shuts down, the rest of

00:02:47.400 --> 00:02:51.550
the body follows. He then puts the fish back,
saying that it's been two years, but the feeling

00:02:51.550 --> 00:02:56.330
doesn't go away. Alice then kisses Adam before
finally confessing that she lives with someone.

00:02:56.330 --> 00:02:59.840
Adam doesn't seem to mind, though, and when
Alice begins putting on her underwear, he

00:02:59.840 --> 00:03:00.840
tells her not to.

00:03:00.840 --> 00:03:04.630
At home, Alice unexpectedly tells Jake that
she has to leave him. Shocked, Jake walks

00:03:04.630 --> 00:03:08.060
up to her and hugs her, and as Alice cries,
Jake insists that they're perfect together

00:03:08.060 --> 00:03:12.230
and that he wants to marry her. Stifling a
sob, she admits that she met somebody, and

00:03:12.230 --> 00:03:15.430
while Jake tries to keep himself from exploding,
all Alice could say is that she didn't mean

00:03:15.430 --> 00:03:19.760
to hurt him. Finally, Jake lets out his anger
and turns over a small table, while Alice

00:03:19.760 --> 00:03:21.820
only listens to him before walking out.

00:03:21.820 --> 00:03:25.770
After heading to Adam's place, Alice meets
his sister, Deborah. She lets Alice know that

00:03:25.770 --> 00:03:29.740
Adam isn't there at the moment before inviting
her inside. There, Deborah explains that Adam's

00:03:29.740 --> 00:03:33.401
having some work done on his place, so he
stayed in her house while she was gone. As

00:03:33.401 --> 00:03:37.380
she arranges her photos, Deborah explains
Adam's aversion to looking at them. Alice

00:03:37.380 --> 00:03:41.290
points to a woman in one of the pictures,
asking if it's Francoise. Deborah confirms

00:03:41.290 --> 00:03:44.430
this and tells her that Adam can't look at
the photos because it's hard for him to see

00:03:44.430 --> 00:03:48.380
Francoise. While he's a brave guy, he can
get scared of remembering, and he forgets

00:03:48.380 --> 00:03:52.100
that the accident wasn't solely his fault.
Deborah adds that she was with the mountaineers

00:03:52.100 --> 00:03:56.319
when the accident happened and that Francoise
was her best friend. Finally, Deborah calls

00:03:56.319 --> 00:03:59.560
Alice by name for the first time, and she
compliments her on her beauty, saying that

00:03:59.560 --> 00:04:04.770
she can see why Adam fell so hard for her.
After that, Alice asks her for Adam's address.

00:04:04.770 --> 00:04:09.270
Upon finding Adam's place, Alice rings his
doorbell several times, but there is no answer.

00:04:09.270 --> 00:04:13.150
When Adam finally shows up, he hugs Alice
tightly as she tells him that she left Jake.

00:04:13.150 --> 00:04:16.220
She starts telling Adam that he's hurting
her, but he ignores this and starts eagerly

00:04:16.220 --> 00:04:20.830
kissing her. As usual, Alice returns his kiss,
ends up against a wall, and the two sleep

00:04:20.830 --> 00:04:25.460
together again. The following morning, Alice
wakes up alone in bed, and when she gets out,

00:04:25.460 --> 00:04:29.790
she sees Adam downstairs just coming in with
a woman. Adam introduces Joanna Noble to Alice,

00:04:29.790 --> 00:04:33.220
and Joanna informs her that she's a reporter
from The Guardian, tasked to interview Adam

00:04:33.220 --> 00:04:35.680
about his Himalayan clean-up project.

00:04:35.680 --> 00:04:39.550
After greeting the reporter, Alice tries looking
for a shirt in Adam's closet but finds it

00:04:39.550 --> 00:04:43.670
locked. Adam watches Alice going through his
drawer and finding a key, only to put it back.

00:04:43.670 --> 00:04:47.260
Finally, she settles on the shirt that's on
the chair, and when Adam's phone rings, she

00:04:47.260 --> 00:04:51.180
informs him about it. Adam then tells her
to answer it for him, and when she does, there's

00:04:51.180 --> 00:04:55.550
nobody on the other line. Soon, Alice tells
him that she needs to go to work, and Adam

00:04:55.550 --> 00:04:58.500
kisses her before asking her to see him afterwards.

00:04:58.500 --> 00:05:02.120
Adam takes Alice wall climbing, where Deborah
sees her and helps her put on her harness.

00:05:02.120 --> 00:05:05.730
As Adam gets down from the wall, he gently
pulls Deborah aside, saying he'll take it

00:05:05.730 --> 00:05:09.050
from there. When he finished helping Alice
with her harness, Alice gets introduced to

00:05:09.050 --> 00:05:11.490
Klaus, and she tells him that she liked his
book.

00:05:11.490 --> 00:05:15.730
Later on, Alice meets up with her friend,
Sylvie. She disapproves of Alice destroying

00:05:15.730 --> 00:05:19.520
her and Jake's lives by letting go of a man
who loves her just for a good bang. Alice

00:05:19.520 --> 00:05:23.450
tries to defend herself by saying that when
she's with Adam, everything is just more.

00:05:23.450 --> 00:05:27.850
As the two leave the bar, a man suddenly mugs
Alice before immediately running away.

00:05:27.850 --> 00:05:31.070
Witnessing the whole thing, Adam chases the
guy and catches up to him by the telephone

00:05:31.070 --> 00:05:34.770
booth, where he smashes the mugger's head
against the glass and beats him up badly.

00:05:34.770 --> 00:05:38.000
Alice and Sylvie catch up to them, and Alice
tells Sylvie to call the cops while she runs

00:05:38.000 --> 00:05:42.389
to Adam, telling him to stop. When Adam finally
relents, he embraces Alice and kisses her

00:05:42.389 --> 00:05:46.040
deeply, promising her that that will never
happen again and that he will protect her.

00:05:46.040 --> 00:05:50.131
The sight shocks Sylvie, but Adam and Alice
pay her no mind and start walking away. Out

00:05:50.131 --> 00:05:54.230
of the blue, Adam proposes to Alice, saying
the sooner they get married, the better, and

00:05:54.230 --> 00:05:55.910
Alice joyfully accepts.

00:05:55.910 --> 00:06:00.270
One day, Alice receives a mysterious letter,
asking her what she really knows about Adam.

00:06:00.270 --> 00:06:03.830
She shows Adam the telegram and informs him
about the call from that morning, saying someone

00:06:03.830 --> 00:06:07.639
was on the line, but they weren't talking.
Adam says someone is just scaring her, and

00:06:07.639 --> 00:06:11.100
as he lets her in his car, he reminds Alice
to tell him if anything like that happens

00:06:11.100 --> 00:06:14.830
again. They then drive to Adam's family church
by the countryside to get married, where they

00:06:14.830 --> 00:06:18.620
have two strangers as their witnesses. After
the ceremony, they get dressed at the way

00:06:18.620 --> 00:06:22.460
station for hikers, where Adam takes a picture
of Alice while still naked.

00:06:22.460 --> 00:06:25.810
They change into their hiking outfits, and
as Alice recalls what she did with Adam to

00:06:25.810 --> 00:06:29.100
celebrate their marriage, the person she's
telling her story to is surprised to learn

00:06:29.100 --> 00:06:32.770
that they went hiking on their wedding day.
As they walk in the wilderness, Alice quickly

00:06:32.770 --> 00:06:36.610
gets worn out and sits down. Because of that,
Adam promises to give her an unforgettable

00:06:36.610 --> 00:06:40.419
honeymoon then teaches her how to conserve
her energy. Adam then goes ahead, leaving

00:06:40.419 --> 00:06:44.410
Alice by herself. Since she wants Adam to
be proud of her, she follows the trail for

00:06:44.410 --> 00:06:47.000
hours until she finally reaches his cabin.

00:06:47.000 --> 00:06:50.770
Inside, Adam makes an anchor and gives Alice
a long piece of silk, explaining that the

00:06:50.770 --> 00:06:54.970
anchor is for catching a falling body. Without
hesitation, Alice lets Adam wrap the silk

00:06:54.970 --> 00:06:58.780
around her neck and hook it on the anchor,
giving him control over her body. She lets

00:06:58.780 --> 00:07:02.960
Adam decide when she can and cannot breathe,
and finally, after making love, Adam tells

00:07:02.960 --> 00:07:06.860
her that he loves her. Alice continues her
story, recounting that they returned to London

00:07:06.860 --> 00:07:10.840
and Joanna Noble's article came out. She was
happier than she'd ever been.

00:07:10.840 --> 00:07:14.630
As Alice gets home one day, she receives another
mysterious letter, warning her that marrying

00:07:14.630 --> 00:07:18.551
Adam was a mistake. She quickly calls Jake
but gets surprised when Sylvie answers the

00:07:18.551 --> 00:07:22.590
phone. Sylvie tells Alice that she and Jake
have been seeing each other, but Alice doesn't

00:07:22.590 --> 00:07:26.810
seem to mind. From the shower, Adam calls
Alice and tells her they'll be late, so Alice

00:07:26.810 --> 00:07:31.160
ends the call with Sylvie. This time, Alice
doesn't show Adam the letter. They attend

00:07:31.160 --> 00:07:35.210
a gathering together, and Alice feels completely
out of place. After looking at a picture of

00:07:35.210 --> 00:07:39.889
Adam with Francoise, Alice goes to the bathroom,
where Deborah sees her wiping off her lipstick.

00:07:39.889 --> 00:07:44.009
When Deborah asks if she's okay, Alice tells
her that she has a headache. To help her,

00:07:44.009 --> 00:07:47.449
Deborah massages her hand and neck, and once
she's better, Alice thanks her sister-in-law.

00:07:47.449 --> 00:07:51.770
Then, Deborah asks Alice to close her eyes,
and when she does, Deborah puts a necklace

00:07:51.770 --> 00:07:56.120
around her neck. Downstairs, Klaus proposes
a toast to Alice, announcing that she has

00:07:56.120 --> 00:07:59.820
conquered Adam. When Adam sees Alice with
his sister, he suddenly gets uncomfortable

00:07:59.820 --> 00:08:01.280
but hugs them both anyway.

00:08:01.280 --> 00:08:04.660
While in a meeting, Alice receives a call
from Joanna and informs her that she's just

00:08:04.660 --> 00:08:08.900
received a weird note about Adam's article.
Alice receives the note through the fax machine.

00:08:08.900 --> 00:08:12.570
It's from a woman who claims that Adam had
defiled her, and she's asking Joanna to report

00:08:12.570 --> 00:08:16.900
the truth. Alice then receives the continuation
of the letter, which shows the name and contact

00:08:16.900 --> 00:08:20.550
number of the sender, Michelle Stowe, who
says that she'll reveal the real story.

00:08:20.550 --> 00:08:24.860
Upset, Alice leaves the office and goes to
Michelle's place. Meanwhile, Adam calls Alice's

00:08:24.860 --> 00:08:29.000
office and learns that she's just left. Posing
as Joanna, Alice interviews Michelle about

00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:33.009
the incident. Michelle recounts it to Alice,
saying she and Adam were kissing at a party

00:08:33.009 --> 00:08:36.499
that time and before she knew it, Adam was
pulling her into the bushes and started forcing

00:08:36.499 --> 00:08:40.740
himself on her until he overpowered her. Michelle
then sarcastically asks Alice if she'll write

00:08:40.740 --> 00:08:44.380
an article about it, adding that they can
make some money out of it. However, Alice

00:08:44.380 --> 00:08:48.389
tells her it doesn't work that way, especially
since she has no proof against Adam. Later

00:08:48.389 --> 00:08:52.860
that day, Alice meets Joanna, who is unhappy
about what Alice did. She tells Alice that

00:08:52.860 --> 00:08:56.800
she could get fired for her carelessness,
and Alice apologizes to her. Alice says she's

00:08:56.800 --> 00:09:01.160
just really curious, but Joanna tells her
that curiosity gets people killed. Alice resolves

00:09:01.160 --> 00:09:05.209
that she should trust Adam, and the two women
prepare to leave. Meanwhile, someone outside

00:09:05.209 --> 00:09:07.110
the coffee shop puts out a cigarette.

00:09:07.110 --> 00:09:10.880
That night, Alice contemplates how little
she knows about Adam. She's musing about how

00:09:10.880 --> 00:09:14.800
everything she knows about him either came
from a book, a newspaper, or even shreds of

00:09:14.800 --> 00:09:18.990
information from other people. With a strong
desire to know more, Alice takes the key that

00:09:18.990 --> 00:09:22.660
she saw in the drawer the other day and opens
Adam's closet. In there, she finds a box of

00:09:22.660 --> 00:09:26.590
letters from a woman named Adele Blanchard.
As she reads them, Alice learns that Adam

00:09:26.590 --> 00:09:30.389
used to have an affair with a married woman.
Adele is telling Adam in her letters that

00:09:30.389 --> 00:09:34.220
she's going back to her husband, and that
what they're doing is dangerous. Suddenly,

00:09:34.220 --> 00:09:37.720
Adam arrives, and Alice hurriedly puts back
the letters inside the closet, struggling

00:09:37.720 --> 00:09:42.689
to close it properly. When she finally does,
Alice greets Adam as if nothing happened.

00:09:42.689 --> 00:09:46.240
The following morning, Adam informs Alice
that he called her office the previous day,

00:09:46.240 --> 00:09:49.689
