stammers that she had a doctor's appointment

00:09:49.689 --> 00:09:54.269
but wasn't able to leave her meeting. Skeptical,
Adam asks where exactly the meeting was held,

00:09:54.269 --> 00:09:58.259
and Alice nervously answers that it was at
The Hilton. Though he remains unconvinced,

00:09:58.259 --> 00:10:02.129
Adam apologizes to her for being nosy. He
then shows Alice her necklace and asks where

00:10:02.129 --> 00:10:06.050
she got it from, and Alice says Deborah gave
it to her. For a moment, there's a trace of

00:10:06.050 --> 00:10:10.069
disbelief and uneasiness on Adam's face, but
it disappears quickly as he smiles, saying

00:10:10.069 --> 00:10:13.610
Deborah has good taste. As Adam reads the
newspaper, Alice tells him about Michelle

00:10:13.610 --> 00:10:17.980
Stowe's note and accusation. Adam is quick
to deny it, saying it never happened, and

00:10:17.980 --> 00:10:21.980
that he's not surprised that Michelle contacted
her. Adam then apologizes to Alice for having

00:10:21.980 --> 00:10:26.910
to hear that story, and before she could reply,
Klaus shows up to take Adam to a talk show.

00:10:26.910 --> 00:10:29.899
Once they're gone, Alice goes through Adam's
drawer again to find the key to the closet,

00:10:29.899 --> 00:10:34.089
but it isn't there. Suddenly, she hears the
sound of the wind chime from the front door,

00:10:34.089 --> 00:10:38.079
and she immediately checks to see if Adam
is back. When she opens the door, Alice finds

00:10:38.079 --> 00:10:41.640
a package on the floor, containing a letter
that asks her how far she'll let Adam go and

00:10:41.640 --> 00:10:46.040
a long piece of silk with bloodstains, similar
to the one Adam used on her during their honeymoon.

00:10:46.040 --> 00:10:49.170
Alice then quickly calls the Directory Inquiries
and asks if they have a listing for Adele

00:10:49.170 --> 00:10:53.640
Blanchard on Marchmont Road. Posing as Joanna
again, Alice goes to Adele's house, where

00:10:53.640 --> 00:10:55.430
Adele's mother greets her.

00:10:55.430 --> 00:10:58.449
Alice learns from her that Adele's been missing
for eight months, and after Adele's mother

00:10:58.449 --> 00:11:02.720
invites her inside, she tells Alice that Adele
hasn't even contacted her husband, Michael.

00:11:02.720 --> 00:11:07.569
Then, she shows her Adele's photo album, where
she finds Adam in one of Adele's wedding pictures.

00:11:07.569 --> 00:11:10.649
Adele's mother says her daughter used to climb
with Adam all the time, but that stopped two

00:11:10.649 --> 00:11:14.569
years after she got married. She says Michael
got fed up with Adele's mountain climbing,

00:11:14.569 --> 00:11:19.019
so in the end, Adele chose to stop. To her
horror, Alice also sees a naked photo of Adele

00:11:19.019 --> 00:11:23.139
standing beside an angel's statue at the place
where they got married. Then, Adele's mother

00:11:23.139 --> 00:11:27.119
mentions that Adam called her, asking for
updates on the investigation. When Adele's

00:11:27.119 --> 00:11:31.389
mother tells Alice that Adam is also coming,
Alice immediately excuses herself and leaves,

00:11:31.389 --> 00:11:35.309
secretly taking two photos of Adele. She throws
away her package before boarding the train

00:11:35.309 --> 00:11:37.509
while repeatedly looking behind her.

00:11:37.509 --> 00:11:41.480
That evening, Alice is startled when she suddenly
sees Adam in the dark corner of their house,

00:11:41.480 --> 00:11:44.749
smoking. Adam then puts out his cigarette
and picks Alice up before binding her on the

00:11:44.749 --> 00:11:49.050
table. Alice tries to protest, but Adam ignores
her and accuses her of being with another

00:11:49.050 --> 00:11:53.480
man. When Alice denies it, Adam asks her why
she keeps sneaking around, and that's when

00:11:53.480 --> 00:11:57.129
she admits that she's found Adele's letters.
Furious, Adam goes upstairs to retrieve the

00:11:57.129 --> 00:12:01.129
letters and starts throwing them down to Alice,
saying he has nothing to hide. When he goes

00:12:01.129 --> 00:12:05.690
back down, Alice asks him to untie her, but
Adam only sits on the floor and cries, lamenting

00:12:05.690 --> 00:12:08.499
over how she wouldn't be in that position
if she trusted him.

00:12:08.499 --> 00:12:11.709
Trying to get Adam's sympathy, Alice says
she just wanted to know him more so that she

00:12:11.709 --> 00:12:15.440
could love him more. While he's crying, Adam
assures Alice that he's hers, and that he

00:12:15.440 --> 00:12:19.709
loves her so much, he can break her neck.
Adam then asks if she likes what they're doing,

00:12:19.709 --> 00:12:23.489
but she doesn't answer his question and instead
tells him that she needs to pee. After Adam

00:12:23.489 --> 00:12:27.199
unties her, Alice escapes his house through
the fire exit, and Adam quickly goes after

00:12:27.199 --> 00:12:31.149
her, begging her to stop. As she hides from
Adam, Alice witnesses how he could lose his

00:12:31.149 --> 00:12:33.499
temper over small things and throw a fit.

00:12:33.499 --> 00:12:37.309
Finally, it's revealed that the person Alice
has been talking to is a Senior Police Officer,

00:12:37.309 --> 00:12:40.490
and she explains that that's when she came
to him. She asks him if they can open Adele

00:12:40.490 --> 00:12:44.920
Blanchard's case, but the officer says it's
not easy to open a case like Adele's. Alice

00:12:44.920 --> 00:12:49.410
retorts that Adam killed Adele, but the officer
says she has no proof of that. Still determined

00:12:49.410 --> 00:12:53.180
to have Adam arrested, Alice tells him that
Adam forced himself on Michelle, but the officer

00:12:53.180 --> 00:12:57.339
curtly replies that Michelle never reported
it. The only proof she has is the two photographs

00:12:57.339 --> 00:13:01.819
of Adele, which prove nothing. The officer
then shows Adam through the double-sided glass,

00:13:01.819 --> 00:13:05.430
telling the officers about Alice's escape
in the other interrogation room. She hears

00:13:05.430 --> 00:13:08.689
Adam saying he loves her, and the officer
tells Alice that even though he believes Adam

00:13:08.689 --> 00:13:12.829
has the potential for violence, he isn't sure
if he's a murderer. After closing the blinds,

00:13:12.829 --> 00:13:16.350
the officer informs Alice that they can only
keep Adam for a few hours, adding that she's

00:13:16.350 --> 00:13:19.050
accusing a hero while providing no evidence.

00:13:19.050 --> 00:13:23.299
With no one to turn to, Alice asks for Deborah's
help to know the truth about Adam. After learning

00:13:23.299 --> 00:13:27.370
from Deborah that Francoise was with someone
else, Alice infers that Francoise left Adam,

00:13:27.370 --> 00:13:30.790
so he killed her. Deborah agrees with her
then she shows Alice two different anchors

00:13:30.790 --> 00:13:34.829
used in climbing, one of which is made of
cheap material. She says Adam could've switched

00:13:34.829 --> 00:13:39.420
the anchors, killing Francoise and her group.
Finally, Deborah advises Alice to leave Adam

00:13:39.420 --> 00:13:44.329
for her own good. Scared, Alice tells Deborah
about Adele and gives her Adele's pictures.

00:13:44.329 --> 00:13:47.430
Alice still thinks that Adam killed her, and
she must've been be buried at the location

00:13:47.430 --> 00:13:51.790
in the picture, at Saint Edmund's. Then, Alice
asks Deborah to come with her to find Adele.

00:13:51.790 --> 00:13:55.670
On their way to Saint Edmund's, Deborah confesses
to sending Alice the notes. She knows about

00:13:55.670 --> 00:13:59.730
Adam's violence, and she wants her to get
away from him. Back at Deborah's place, Adam

00:13:59.730 --> 00:14:03.559
finds the two photos of Adele, and after quickly
realizing where Alice is headed, he follows

00:14:03.559 --> 00:14:07.540
her. At Saint Edmund's, Alice finds a body
buried in the dirt, wearing a necklace like

00:14:07.540 --> 00:14:11.360
the one Deborah gave her. When Alice confronts
her about it, Deborah ominously says that

00:14:11.360 --> 00:14:15.049
Adele didn't have to die if only she'd told
her that she was going back to Michael. With

00:14:15.049 --> 00:14:18.639
a sneer, Deborah says she gave Adele a necklace,
too, and that she found it beautiful just

00:14:18.639 --> 00:14:22.639
like Alice did. With Alice demanding to know
what Deborah did, the two women start fighting

00:14:22.639 --> 00:14:23.869
and hitting each other.

00:14:23.869 --> 00:14:26.819
Deborah aggressively admits to sleeping with
her brother when they were kids, adding that

00:14:26.819 --> 00:14:30.809
she's the one who gave him his first piece
of silk. As they struggle, Deborah yells that

00:14:30.809 --> 00:14:34.009
Adam is hers and attempts to hit Alice with
a shovel, but Adam shows up and tackles her

00:14:34.009 --> 00:14:37.980
to the ground. Alice then runs away, and Adam
hits Deborah across the face, saying he was

00:14:37.980 --> 00:14:41.929
never hers. As he starts looking for Alice,
Deborah is about to hit him at the back with

00:14:41.929 --> 00:14:45.939
a shovel, but Alice shoots her with a flare
gun. Deborah dies in Adam's arms, leaving

00:14:45.939 --> 00:14:49.629
him stunned and devastated. He confesses to
Alice that he and Deborah used to go there

00:14:49.629 --> 00:14:53.989
together, and with a betrayed look, Adam says
that he thought Alice just had to trust him.

00:14:53.989 --> 00:14:57.500
Deborah's body is taken by the cops the following
day, and so is Adam.

00:14:57.500 --> 00:15:01.230
Two years later, Alice and Adam see each other
again at the airport, as he is going up the

00:15:01.230 --> 00:15:04.779
escalator while she is going down. Neither
of them says anything, but they just look

00:15:04.779 --> 00:15:08.819
at each other. When Adam reaches the top,
he stays there for a moment and looks at Alice

00:15:08.819 --> 00:15:13.189
one last time before walking away. Meanwhile,
Alice starts thinking that a flatlander like

00:15:13.189 --> 00:15:20.790
her can't live at a high altitude, right where
Adam is.

